featured_reviews.review_id:
The place to go for "The Faithful". Caters to the needs of the locality. Being a Muslim majority area, all the shopkeepers and the populace who happen to be in the vicinity during the muezzin's call make their way to the mosque here.

The mosque is two storied and make entirely by the donations and support of the local folk. Religion is a thing that binds us, and this mosque does exactly this. You must see the crowd on the weekly Jummah Namaaz (Friday prayers) to understand the importance that faith has in our lives.
